@startuml Authentication Flow with Role-Based Redirect
title Authentication Flow with Role-Based Redirect

actor User as U
participant "Frontend (React/Remix)" as FE
participant "Backend (API)" as BE
participant "Auth Service" as Auth
participant "Browser Cookie Store" as Cookie

== User Sign-In ==
U -> FE: Enter email & password
FE -> BE: POST /login { email, password }

== Backend Validation ==
BE -> Auth: validateCredentials(email, password)
Auth --> BE: user object (userId, email, role)

== JWT Creation ==
BE -> Auth: generateJwtToken({ userId, email, role })
Auth --> BE: JWT token

== Set HttpOnly Cookie ==
BE -> Cookie: Set-Cookie: authToken=JWT (HttpOnly, SameSite, Secure)
BE --> FE: 200 OK { success: true, role }

== Frontend Role Handling ==
FE -> FE: decode JWT from cookie
FE -> FE: check token.role

alt role == "agent" or "admin"
    FE -> FE: navigate("/dashboard")
else role == "user"
    FE -> FE: navigate(`/profile/${userId}`)
end

== Post-Login State ==
FE -> Cookie: browser sends authToken automatically on requests
FE -> BE: authenticated requests with cookie

@enduml
